	London, Apr. 22 (PTI): Pamela Andersons dream job is to play the Bond Girl in a 007 movie. The former Baywatch star admits that a role in the spy series is one of her lifes ambitions, the Daily Star reported.         
	The 42-year-old mother of two is currently starring on Dancing With The Stars in the US and insists she wants to prepare to step into the shoes of the Bond Girl.               
	 London (PTI): Helen Mirren is tired of filmmakers casting British actors as villains in Hollywood films. The 64-year-old actress has slammed movie bosses for frequently portraying baddies on the big screen with a UK accent, insisting not all Brits are stuck-up, malevolent characters, Contactmusic reported.                                                                                                                                                          
